# Session Quality — Startup + Skills Every Time

**Do not rely on long chat history.** Repo docs + skills are source of truth.

## 1. Every new session (before any action)

Read in order (use Read tool — do not skip):

1. `AGENTS.md` — current phase, tests, checklist
2. Latest `plan/handoff-*.md` (now: `plan/handoff-cfpb-20260611.md`)
3. If task touches a shipped WP: its `plan/wp*-report.md` or `docs/*.md`

If handoff conflicts with chat, **handoff + AGENTS.md win**.

## 2. Before acting — invoke the matching skill

Read `.agents/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` **first** when trigger matches. **Never improvise** when a skill applies.

**User may speak in plain Thai/English** — do NOT require `/pipeline-ops` or other slash prefixes. Infer intent and load the skill (e.g. "เช็คสถานะ", "pipeline ok ไหม", "queue ค้างไหม" → `pipeline-ops`).

Optional shortcuts for humans: `.cursor/commands/` → user types `/` and picks `/status`, `/cfpb`, `/help`. See `plan/cursor-copy-paste.md`.

| Situation | Skill |
|---|---|
| Pipeline / stations / queue / CFPB / Telegram ops | `pipeline-ops` |
| New feature or bugfix in code | `tdd` |
| Bug, failure, regression | `diagnose` |
| End of phase or session handoff | `handoff` |
| Review before merge/commit | `review` |
| Plan before big build | read `PLAN.md`; user `/octo-plan` → follow octo workflow |
| Hermes review gate | `hermes-dispatch` |
| User wants terse replies | `caveman` |

Full skill table: `.cursor/rules/project-skills.mdc`.

## 3. Quality gates (before claiming "done")

- Run `.venv\Scripts\pytest` for code changes
- Run migrate smoke if schema changed: `python -c "from shared.db import migrate; migrate('data/test.db')"`
- CFPB/ops: query live DB via `docker exec radio-worker` or `.\scripts\pipeline-status.ps1` — **not** host `data/pipeline.db` during Docker ingest
- Update `plan/` report or handoff when closing a work package
- Do not commit unless user asks

## 4. Context discipline

- Prefer **short answers** + pointers to `plan/` and `docs/`
- Summarize session end → `plan/handoff-*.md` (use `handoff` skill)
- Library how-to → Context7 MCP; live facts → Exa MCP (see `project-plugins-mcp.mdc`)
